Psalm 108-1 <pb/><t><f>ⓐ</f> My heart is steadfast, O God! </t><t>I will sing and make melody with all my being! <f>[1]</f></t>
Psalm 108-2 <t>Awake, O harp and lyre! </t><t>I will awake the dawn!</t>
Psalm 108-3 <t>I will give thanks to you, O LORD, among the peoples; </t><t>I will sing praises to you among the nations.</t>
Psalm 108-4 <t>For your steadfast love is great <f>ⓑ</f>above the heavens; </t><t>your faithfulness reaches to the clouds. </t>
Psalm 108-5 <pb/><t>Be exalted, O God, above the heavens! </t><t>Let your glory be over all the earth!</t>
Psalm 108-6 <t><f>ⓒ</f> That your beloved ones may be delivered, </t><t>give salvation by your right hand and answer me! </t>
Psalm 108-7 <pb/><t>God has promised in his holiness: <f>[2]</f> </t><t>“With exultation I will divide up Shechem </t><t>and portion out the Valley of Succoth.</t>
Psalm 108-8 <t>Gilead is mine; Manasseh is mine; </t><t>Ephraim is my helmet, </t><t>Judah my scepter.</t>
Psalm 108-9 <t>Moab is my washbasin; </t><t>upon Edom I cast my shoe; </t><t><f>ⓓ</f>over Philistia I shout in triumph.” </t>
Psalm 108-10 <pb/><t>Who will bring me to the fortified city? </t><t>Who will lead me to Edom?</t>
Psalm 108-11 <t>Have you not rejected us, O God? </t><t>You do not go out, O God, with our armies.</t>
Psalm 108-12 <t>Oh grant us help against the foe, </t><t>for vain is the salvation of man!</t>
Psalm 108-13 <t>With God we shall do valiantly; </t><t>it is he who will tread down our foes. </t>